[h1]Support Deleting Items[/h1]

To add an Edit button to the table view, find the [b]viewDidLoad()[/b] method in [i]ItemTableViewController.swift[/i], and add the following code:[code format="swift"]navigationItem.leftBarButtonItem = editButtonItem()[/code]
Run the app, and notice that there's an Edit button on the left of the table view's navigation bar. Click the button, and the table view goes into editing mode:  [img id="1058" width="60%"] 
To actually delete an item, find and uncomment the[b] tableView(_:commitEditingStyle:forRowAtIndexPath:)[/b] method. The template implementation looks like this: [code format="swift"]// Override to support editing the table view.
override func tableView(tableView: UITableView, commitEditingStyle editingStyle: UITableViewCellEditingStyle, forRowAtIndexPath indexPath: NSIndexPath) {
  if editingStyle == .Delete {
    
    tableView.deleteRowsAtIndexPaths([indexPath], withRowAnimation: .Fade)
  } else if editingStyle == .Insert {
    
  }
}[/code]
In the [b]if editingStyle = .Delete [/b]condition add the following: [code format="swift"][b]items.removeAtIndex(indexPath.row)[/b]
tableView.deleteRowsAtIndexPaths([indexPath], withRowAnimation: .Fade)[/code]
This removes the selected item from our [b]items [/b]list.
Run the app to see the delete function in action! [img id="1059" width="60%"]
